                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 30: Mobile phone users can switch service providers without changing their cell numbers only after 90 days of getting a connection, the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India said in its draft regulations on number portability. The draft lays down the process of implementing number portability and covered areas such as subscribers eligibility conditions and the rights and duties of the service providers.                             
	 Mumbai, June 30: State-run oil firms today raised jet fuel price by over 6 per cent, the fourth time in two months. Indian Oil, Bharat Petroleum and Hindustan Petroleum raised rates by Rs 2,306 to Rs 38,558 per kilolitre in Delhi. Jet fuel in Calcutta will be dearer at Rs 46,711 per kl from Rs 44,289 per kl.                             
	 New Delhi, June 30: Mukesh Ambani-run Reliance Industries has rejected offer for talks and told Anil Ambani group firm RNRL that it would not sign any agreement on the gas supply issue without the approval of the government.                            
	 New Delhi, June 30: Indian Oil Corporation plans to invest about Rs 60,000 crore to expand its refining capacity to 80 million tonnes by 2011-12, refinery director B.N. Bankapur said.                                                                                                                           
